theorem
fixes f :: "int \<Rightarrow> int" and inv_f :: "int \<Rightarrow> int"
assumes h0 : "bij f"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. f x = (case x of 1 \<Rightarrow> 3 | 2 \<Rightarrow> 13 | 3 \<Rightarrow> 8 | 5 \<Rightarrow> 1 | 8 \<Rightarrow> 0 | 13 \<Rightarrow> 5 | _ \<Rightarrow> undefined)"
and h2 : "inv_f = inv f"

a_9.informal problem: A function $f$ is defined as follows: $f(1) = 3$, $f(2) = 13$, $f(3) = 8$, $f(5) = 1$, $f(8) = 0$, $f(13) = 5$, and is undefined for other values. Find the value of the expression $\frac{f^{-1}(f^{-1}(5) + f^{-1}(13))}{f^{-1}(1)}$. The final answer is $1$.
